Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root. Peel
and then chop into ½cm chunks (or as small as you can!). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Thinly slice the
@chestnut mushrooms{1}. Pull the leaves from the sprigs of @tarragon{1} and
finely chop them. Discard the stalks. Finally, slice the @streaky bacon rashers{10}
into pieces roughly 1cm wide.

Fill a #pot{} with @water{750%ml} and put on high heat. Stir in the
@chicken stock pot{1} and when it's dissolved, reduce the heat to low to keep
your stock hot.

Put a wide bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat and add a glug of
@oil{}. Add your onion and bacon and cook for ~{5-7%minutes} or until your bacon
is nicely browned and your onion is soft. Add your mushrooms and cook for
another ~{3%minutes}.

Add half your garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} and then stir in the @risotto rice{350%g}.
Add the @white wine vinegar{1} and allow it to evaporate completely before adding
your stock. Reduce the heat to low, cover the pan with a #lid{} or seal the pan
with #foil{}. Pop the pan in your oven and cook for ~{25%minutes}. This is your
risotto.

While your risotto is in your oven, get your washing up done and get organised
to finish the meal.

When the time is up, remove your risotto from your oven and leave to cool for
~{5%minutes}. To make the creamed spinach, heat a large #frying pan{} on high
heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Add the @baby spinach{2} to the pan, season
with a pinch of @salt{} and a generous grind of @black pepper{} and stir
continually for ~{2%minutes} or until your spinach has wilted.

> You may need to cook your spinach in batches.

Once all your spinach has wilted, add it all back to the pan with your remaining
garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Finish your baby spinach by stirring in the
@crème fraîche{1} and then keep to one side.

Take the lid off your risotto and stir in the @unsalted butter{30%g} and half of
the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Add a squeeze of @lemon{1} and your
tarragon. Taste to make sure you are happy with the seasoning. Add more salt and
pepper if necessary.

Serve your risotto in deep #bowls{} with a spoonful of spinach on top and a
final sprinkle of cheese. Enjoy!